body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Morris Automotive. My name is David Morris. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Barbara. Could you please provide me with your date of birth, including the month and year?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my birthdate is one four zero three, nineteen ninety-two.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Barbara. Can you also confirm the last four digits of your social security number, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, the last four digits are seven eight nine zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great. Thank you for providing that information, Barbara. Is there anything else you would like to share or ask about today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, I think that covers everything. I'm feeling excited about a potential purchase.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: That's wonderful to hear! Thank you for your time, Barbara. If you have any further questions, feel free to reach out. Have a great day!
